<subSubSection id="C37A14E8FF83FFC6FF0A0257FA31FD93" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" type="key">
<keyStep id="30945FC6FF83FFC6FF0A0257FA31FE68" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A0257FA31FE94" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,348,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A0257FA31FE94" box="[136,1451,348,370]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">1. Leaves lobed to deeply lobed .............................................................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A0273FA31FE68" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,377,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A0273FA31FE68" box="[136,1451,377,399]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">1’. Leaves shallowly 3-lobed...................................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30945FC6FF83FFC6FF0A029CFA31FE2E" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A029CFA31FE4D" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,406,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A029CFA31FE4D" box="[136,1451,406,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
2. Bracts and stipules with lacerate-dentate margin, both faces glabrous ...........................................................................1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FAC6029DFA31FE4D" authorityName="Killip" authorityYear="1938" box="[1348,1451,406,428]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setulosa">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FAC6029DFA31FE4D" box="[1348,1451,406,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. setulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A02B9FA31FE2E" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,435,457]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A02B9FA31FE2E" box="[136,1451,435,457]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">2’. Bracts and stipules with dentate to pinnatifid margin, both faces sparsely to densely pilose ............................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30945FC6FF83FFC6FF0A02DAFA31FDDA" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A02DAFA30FDE7" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A02DAFA30FDE7" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
3. Petioles with 3 to 8 pedicellate glands; stipules densely villous, margin deeply gland-tipped to long-stipitate; leaf blades densely pubescent on abaxial surface; ovary and fruits hirsute to pubescents .....................................................................2. 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FA9402E7FA30FDE7" authorityName="Masters" authorityYear="1872" box="[1302,1450,492,514]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campanulata">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FA9402E7FA30FDE7" box="[1302,1450,492,514]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. campanulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A0103FA31FDDA" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A0103FA31FDDA" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
3’. Petioles without glands; stipules sparsely hirsute, margin slightly dentate gland-tipped; leaf blades sparingly hirsute on abaxial surface; ovary and fruits glabrous .......................................................................................................................... 3. 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FA91012DFA31FDDA" box="[1299,1451,551,572]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caparaoensis">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FA91012DFA31FDDA" box="[1299,1451,551,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. caparaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30945FC6FF83FFC6FF0A0149FA31FD93" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A0149FA31FDBE" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,579,601]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A0149FA31FDBE" box="[136,1451,579,601]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
4’. Petioles with 2 to 6 stipitate glands; ovary hirsute .......................................................................................................... 4. 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FACB014EFA31FDBE" authorityName="Gardner" authorityYear="1845" box="[1353,1451,579,601]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vellozoi">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FACB014EFA31FDBE" box="[1353,1451,579,601]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. vellozoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF4763FF83FFC6FF0A016AFA31FD93" blockId="2.[136,1451,348,630]" box="[136,1451,608,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
<keyLead id="3091E456FF83FFC6FF0A016AFA31FD93" box="[136,1451,608,630]" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">
4. Petioles without glands; ovary glabrous............................................................................................................................ 5. 
<taxonomicName id="4C603CE0FF83FFC6FAD1016AFA31FD93" authorityName="Vellozo" authorityYear="1831" box="[1363,1451,608,629]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Passifloraceae" genus="Passiflora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="141" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis id="B9149B71FF83FFC6FAD1016AFA31FD93" box="[1363,1451,608,629]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="141">P. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
